In England, in the seven days to 15 November, there were 228,038 new confirmed cases (403.2 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 08 November, there were 190,804 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 20% (37,234 extra cases). The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in England so far as at 20 November is 8,316,395 (14,706.2 cases per 100,000 population).
